events.body:
@brunoerg: @furszy: Thanks for your reviews, will include both your nits in a bit.

> Seems that this only add coverage for the `target < chain_pow_limit` rule but not for the other validation checks inside `CheckProofOfWork`. What if we extend it to cover all of them?

Considering that we have [quite detailled  `CheckProofOfWork` unit tests](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/1313b9073574be0c7d859ebd6bab2bd09192fe6d/src/test/pow_tests.cpp#L81) that check all those invalid causes already, I think triggering one of them for the purpose of increasing p2p disconnection coverage should be sufficient.
